00:17:11,963 --> 00:17:14,826
You should rather punish them.

277
00:17:14,828 --> 00:17:15,823
How could you appoint them?

278
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:18,745
This is ridiculous!

279
00:17:18,745 --> 00:17:20,318
Work with Lee Yin Jwa?

280
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:22,282
Watch what you're saying!

281
00:17:22,576 --> 00:17:24,183
He didn't say anything wrong.

282
00:17:24,183 --> 00:17:26,118
What nonsense are you saying?

283
00:17:40,389 --> 00:17:43,800
So? How are the senior officials
reacting?

284
00:17:44,674 --> 00:17:46,408
Both Patriarchs and Disciples...

285
00:17:46,410 --> 00:17:48,118
are furious.

286
00:17:48,777 --> 00:17:51,588
Appointing Namins would seem
preposterous to them.

287
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:57,100
The King seems to be starting
a difficult fight.

288
00:17:57,995 --> 00:17:59,149
The whole palace...

289
00:17:59,151 --> 00:18:02,035
might become his enemy.

290
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,154
Your Majesty,

291
00:18:07,566 --> 00:18:09,608
how about taking
things a bit slowly?

292
00:18:10,113 --> 00:18:12,087
We just resolved the crisis...

293
00:18:12,429 --> 00:18:14,259
and we have not arrested
Prince Milpoong yet.

294
00:18:14,289 --> 00:18:15,706
There is still disorder...

295
00:18:15,706 --> 00:18:17,443
That is why we should carry on
with it now.

296
00:18:20,425 --> 00:18:21,886
The state of confusion...

297
00:18:22,581 --> 00:18:25,118
is the right time to carry on
with the reform.

298
00:18:27,175 --> 00:18:28,389
What do you mean?

299
00:18:30,409 --> 00:18:33,692
I am still a helplessly powerless
king.

300
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,900
The only thing I can rely on...

301
00:18:36,738 --> 00:18:37,707
is public opinion.

302
00:18:38,269 --> 00:18:39,570
The revolt ended a few days ago...

303
00:18:39,572 --> 00:18:41,784
and the officials are in a turf war.

304
00:18:41,786 --> 00:18:43,407
What would the people think?

305
00:18:43,988 --> 00:18:45,022
Public opinion...

306
00:18:45,024 --> 00:18:45,956
(Lee Gwang Jwa, Minister of War,
Disciples)

307
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,523
Are you trying to gain power
by moving public opinion?

308
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,484
Thousands were killed in the revolt.

309
00:18:50,909 --> 00:18:52,464
They are all families...

310
00:18:52,466 --> 00:18:54,036
and relatives of the people.

311
00:18:54,870 --> 00:18:56,094
This is the state we are in...

312
00:18:56,738 --> 00:18:58,338
and the officials are protesting...

313
00:18:59,073 --> 00:19:00,309
when I suggested...

314
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:02,197
we appoint Namins.

315
00:19:04,991 --> 00:19:05,940
The fury...

316
00:19:07,402 --> 00:19:08,174
will certainly...

317
00:19:09,253 --> 00:19:11,202
spread outside the palace.

318
00:19:21,136 --> 00:19:22,174
Court Lady Cheon.

319
00:19:25,904 --> 00:19:27,631
Court Lady Heo, how is His Majesty?

320
00:19:27,724 --> 00:19:29,361
May I see him for a moment?

321
00:19:29,361 --> 00:19:31,084
It will not be possible
at the moment.

322
00:19:31,091 --> 00:19:32,998
He has been in a meeting
all the while.

323
00:19:34,402 --> 00:19:35,285
You would know too.

324
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:38,159
The palace is in an uproar.

325
00:19:42,316 --> 00:19:44,768
The disciples defended the palace
during the revolt.

326
00:19:45,011 --> 00:19:45,797
Then,

327
00:19:45,799 --> 00:19:48,020
how can he give the position
to Namins?

328
00:19:48,022 --> 00:19:49,930
The Patriarchs have an advantage
over us anyway.

329
00:19:50,053 --> 00:19:51,642
We cannot step back any further.

330
00:19:52,425 --> 00:19:53,319
We Disciples...

331
00:19:54,347 --> 00:19:55,996
are losing the turf war.

332
00:19:56,823 --> 00:19:58,314
Is that what you want to protest?

333
00:19:58,488 --> 00:20:01,119
My lord, that is not what
I am saying.

334
00:20:02,073 --> 00:20:04,666
Go on. What else...

335
00:20:04,983 --> 00:20:06,863
do you want me to tell the King?

336
00:20:11,839 --> 00:20:14,683
Is it true that you agreed to
appointing the Namins?

337
00:20:14,806 --> 00:20:16,159
That was the only way...

338
00:20:16,161 --> 00:20:17,625
to quench the revolt.

339
00:20:17,627 --> 00:20:19,301
The King will demand us...

340
00:20:19,303 --> 00:20:21,404
to hand over the next offices.

341
00:20:21,718 --> 00:20:23,008
How can the head of
the Patriarchs...

342
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:24,948
make such a compromise?

343
00:20:24,948 --> 00:20:26,066
It was not compromise.

344
00:20:26,068 --> 00:20:27,811
(Min Jin Heon, Chairman of Congress,
Patriarchs)

345
00:20:27,813 --> 00:20:28,935
It was politics.

346
00:20:32,081 --> 00:20:34,135
That was the better choice.

347
00:20:36,144 --> 00:20:37,821
I should not have done so...

348
00:20:38,479 --> 00:20:39,907
as the head of Patriarchs.

349
00:20:42,053 --> 00:20:43,969
I do not deserve to lead you any
longer.

350
00:20:44,855 --> 00:20:46,084
I will resign.

351
00:20:47,605 --> 00:20:48,933
Will that satisfy you?

352
00:20:48,935 --> 00:20:50,045
My lord.

353
00:20:50,047 --> 00:20:51,191
- My lord.
- My lord.

354
00:20:51,193 --> 00:20:52,602
- My lord.
- My lord.

355
00:20:53,775 --> 00:20:55,869
What are we to do?

356
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,046
Go and summon Chief Inspector
of Saheonbu.

357
00:20:59,051 --> 00:21:01,263
- Right now, hurry.
- Yes, my lord.

358
00:21:04,863 --> 00:21:06,738
We heard the news from the palace,
Chief Inspector.

359
00:21:06,738 --> 00:21:09,931
Gather all the officials
of Daejangcheong immediately.

360
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:11,268
Yes.

361
00:21:13,690 --> 00:21:15,211
It will be Saheonbu.

362
00:21:16,269 --> 00:21:18,575
Saheonbu will start moving first
since it has judicial power.

363
00:21:19,104 --> 00:21:20,447
Saganwon and Hongmoongwan...

364
00:21:20,924 --> 00:21:22,353
will give support.

365
00:21:23,456 --> 00:21:26,409
The Patriarchs have controlled
the three agencies for that purpose.

366
00:21:28,066 --> 00:21:29,562
I am preparing for that.

367
00:21:33,042 --> 00:21:34,001
You are...

368
00:21:35,238 --> 00:21:36,874
in a difficult situation
because of me.

369
00:21:37,979 --> 00:21:40,483
That is not true, Your Majesty.

370
00:21:43,034 --> 00:21:44,361
I am rather...

371
00:21:45,363 --> 00:21:46,905
feeling relieved.

372
00:21:47,454 --> 00:21:49,221
You are the one in a difficult
situation.

373
00:21:51,487 --> 00:21:53,330
Fair appointment regardless of
political orientation...

374
00:21:54,573 --> 00:21:55,648
and equity.

375
00:21:59,558 --> 00:22:01,016
That is a dream...

376
00:22:02,308 --> 00:22:03,860
I once dreamed of.

377
00:22:06,066 --> 00:22:08,127
It is just that I realized...

378
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:10,514
